Rating: 3
Based on earlier comments that the coulis wasn't flavorful enough, I added some chicken broth and lemon juice to ours. It was excellent. We'll definitely be making this again.

Rating: 3
Made this for company and it was very good. The coulis needed a fair amount of salt but had a lovely garlicky rich flavour. I kept the coulis fairly thick so it didn't run into everything. Used panko instead of regular bread crumbs which gave it nice crispiness. Breaded the fish a couple hours ahead and just popped it in the oven before the salad. The cooking time as stated by others definitely wrong. About 20 minutes was needed. Made it with soft polenta which contrasted the crispy panko. Very good dish to make entertaining since there is no work to be done last minute.

Rating: 3
I made this dish for my college roommates. It was a good do-ahead dish (made the coulis and bread crumb mixture ahead of time). I agree with others that you want to season the halibut well before adding the breadcrumbs. In addition, the tomato coulis could have used some more flavor/zip. I also ended up cooking the fish about 17 minutes, and one thick piece was still under cooked. My girlfriends thought it was good and I would definitely make it again, with a few slight adjustments.

